    "-Learning from Demonstration (LfD), where the target control agent learns from the demonstrations of the expert by observing their actions and the resulting state transitions.",
    "However, unlike in pure IL, the expert controller in LfD can inform the target agent about the chosen set of actions.",
    "Additionally, in LfD, the target agent may have access to reward signals associated with the actions selected by the expert.",
